On Windows, it is possible to redirect the stdout from Tomcat by starting it with:

{code}
catalina.bat run 1>myfile.txt
{code}

This is useful when attempting to capture threaddumps as the contents of the dump is outputted to the file specified.

However, we need to investigate how to configure this for the *startup.bat* batch file also. 

It would be good to have all output redirected to a log file.

